devdoc.details: keeps the deployed contracts in the arrays names and addressesit keeps two copies of such arrays, and a pointer that points to the "active" copythis is to allow the pattern: "first add the new data, which can cost a lot of gas...and, in one atomic transaction, just change the pointer".We use this to let the Proxy upgrade this Directory as part of the proxy upgrade, atomically.We keep track of deployBlockNum as a safety measure, to ensure that the contracts-to-become-activewere deployed later thant he currently active contracts. Otherwise, we need to call "revertActivation"
